======================================================================
1) Affected Software

* LibRaw 0.x

======================================================================
2) Severity

Rating: Highly critical
Impact: Denial of Service and System Access
Where:  From remote

======================================================================
3) Description of Vulnerability

Secunia Research has discovered a vulnerability in LibRaw, which can
be exploited by malicious people to cause a DoS (Denial of Service)
and compromise a vulnerable system.

1) An error within the "parse_tiff_ifd()" function
(internal/dcraw_common.cpp) can be exploited to corrupt memory.

The vulnerability is confirmed in version 0.18.1. Prior versions may
also be affected.

======================================================================
4) Solution

Apply update.
http://www.libraw.org/news/libraw-0-18-2

======================================================================
5) Time Table

2017/03/08 - Vendor notified about vulnerability.
2017/03/08 - Vendor response.
2017/03/09 - Release of vendor patch.
2017/03/10 - Release of Secunia Advisory SA75737.
2017/05/11 - Public disclosure of Secunia Research Advisory.

======================================================================
6) Credits

Jakub Jirasek, Secunia Research at Flexera Software.

